"If E is present and has a .keys() method, then does:  for k in E.keys(): "
"D[k] = E[k] If E is present and lacks a .keys() method, then does:  for k, v"
" in E: D[k] = v In either case, this is followed by: for k in F:  D[k] = "
"F[k]"
msgstr ""
"If E is present and has a .keys() method, then does: for k in E.keys(): D[k]"
" = E[k] If E is present and lacks a .keys() method, then does: for k, v in "
"E: D[k] = v In either case, this is followed by: for k in F: D[k] = F[k]"

